The paper describes a deep learning model for information extraction in the context of systematic reviews. This falls under the domain of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML), which are covered by several sub-categories in arXiv CS. cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category, as it specifically deals with NLP and its applications. cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely, as the paper describes a deep learning model. cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also possible categories, as they cover related topics such as text mining, information extraction, and neural networks.
